---

🔴 Actual Problem

From your logs:

cannot listen on the TCP port: listen tcp4 :8443: bind: address already in use

👉 Port 8443 is already occupied 👉 So Quay cannot start → exits with 126


---

🔍 Why this is happening

Your output shows:

0.0.0.0:8443->8443/tcp

And the pod is stuck in Created state with leftover infra container.

👉 This means:

A previous failed pod/container is still holding port 8443

Systemd keeps retrying → conflict continues



---

✅ Fix (Clean and Resolve Port Conflict)

Step 1: Stop everything cleanly

systemctl stop quay-app
systemctl stop quay-pod


---

Step 2: Remove stuck pod + containers (IMPORTANT)

podman pod rm -f quay-pod
podman rm -f $(podman ps -aq)


---

Step 3: Verify port 8443 is free

ss -lntp | grep 8443

👉 If you still see something, kill it:

fuser -k 8443/tcp


---

Step 4: Restart installation cleanly

./mirror-registry install \
  --initUser sysadmin \
  --initPassword samsung123


---

⚡ Optional (Safer cleanup if still issues)

If problem persists:

podman system prune -a -f


---

🔥 Why your install failed earlier

First attempt partially created pod

Pod reserved port 8443

New container couldn’t bind → crash loop


👉 This is a very common mirror-registry issue


